 the beginning of every Games there is usually two or three issues - the big one this time is the food in the village, which is not adequate,' Team GB's chief executive Andy Anson said.\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 610, \"end\": 617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 0.6606052759541684, \"rank\": 0.5137091885297075, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andy Anson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the beginning\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"every Games\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"two or three issues\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 533}, {\"ngram\": \"the big one\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"the food\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'There are not enough of certain foods: eggs, chicken, certain carbohydrates, and then there is the quality of the food, with raw meat being served to athletes.\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 814, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"certain foods\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"eggs\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"chicken\", \"from\": 700, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"certain carbohydrates\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"the quality\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"the food\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"raw meat\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'They have got to improve it over the next couple of days dramatically.'\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 888, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next couple\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 865}, {\"ngram\": \"days\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Games' caterer Sodexo Live has promised to address the issues raised, the British Olympic Association have taken matters into their own hands to ensure their athletes stay in top condition.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}, {\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999613910406565, \"rank\": 2.135478527939184e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the issues\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"matters\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1020}, {\"ngram\": \"their own hands\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1041}, {\"ngram\": \"their athletes\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"top condition\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They had already hired an entire catering college in the Paris suburb Clichy, around a 15 minute bus ride from the Olympic Village, for Team GB to use as a performance base.\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1148, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999722604, \"rank\": 2.78406059659147e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1161, \"end\": 1167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.549373172604347e-21, \"text\": \"Clichy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\"}, {\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.696958853656162e-14, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an entire catering college\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"a 15 minute bus ride\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"Team GB\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"a performance base\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, given the food in the village, it has been revealed that the athletes are now almost exclusively going to the base for their meals, with additional chefs having to be brought in in order to meet demand.\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the food\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"the base\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"their meals\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"additional chefs\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1428}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1461}, {\"ngram\": \"demand\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1476}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Our athletes have decided they would rather go and eat in our performance lodge in Clichy, so we are having to get another chef to come over as the demand is far exceeding what we thought it would be,' Anson added.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1563, \"end\": 1569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bo